Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, indicating impaired renal function, and mild elevation of ALT, suggesting possible liver involvement. Urinalysis reveals significant proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, raising concern for nephrotic syndrome or diabetic nephropathy. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Further clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation are recommended.
